          <Comment>In summary, the currently available evidence indicates that the variant is pathogenic, but additional data are needed to prove that conclusively. Therefore, this variant has been classified as Likely Pathogenic. Loss-of-function variants in COL6A1 are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 19884007, 20976770). This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals with COL6A1-related conditions. This variant is not present in population databases (ExAC no frequency). This variant results in the deletion of part of exon 2 (c.98-2_103del) of the COL6A1 gene. It is expected to disrupt RNA splicing and likely results in an absent or disrupted protein product.</Comment>
